ENTRY            F1084   20260113   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F1084001   20260113   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 10         35
TITLE      Nuclear interaction dynamics in Fe-56(alpha,xn)
           reaction
AUTHOR     (B.V.Zhuravlev,N.N.Titarenko,V.I.Trykova)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSFEI)
REFERENCE  (S,ISINN-16,237,2009) Additional data at 12.3, 16.3 MeV
           Other data presented in this publication compiled in
           Entries F0730, A0101, A0276, A0830 (see REL-REF).
           (J,BAS,64,331,2000) English translation
           (J,IZV,64,414,2000)
           (J,BAS,62,93,1998) English translation
           (J,IZV,62,110,1998)
REL-REF    (O,F0730001,B.V.Zhuravlev,J,IZV,64,414,2000) Neutron
           spectra for the incident alpha energies of 16.3 and
           18.3 MeV are compiled.
           (O,A0101001,N.S.Birjukov+,C,80KIEV,2,30,1980) Neutron
           spectra for the incident alpha energies of 45.2 MeV
           are compiled (data from authors).
           (O,A0276001,N.S.Birjukov+,C,83KIEV,3,290,1983) Neutron
           spectra for the incident alpha energies of 26.8 MeV
           are compiled (data from authors).
           (O,A0832007,B.V.Zhuravlev+,S,ISINN-6,151,1998) - Level
                                               density presented.
DETECTOR   (SCIN) Neutrons were detected by the scintillation
           counter. For decreasing of the background it was
           placed in the massive shielding, and electronic
           discrimination of gamma-rays was performed.
SAMPLE     Self-supporting metal foils with the thicknesses of
           0.6 mg/cm2 and 2.6 mg/cm2 and enrichment of 99.5% were
           used as the targets.
METHOD     (TOF,BCINT)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
HISTORY    (20101125C)
           (20260113A) SD: Corrections in all Subents. Several
           Subents were merged. Subents 010, 011 deleted (data
           from authors presented in A0101027 and A0276019).
ENDBIB              35
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           38
SUBENT        F1084002   20260113   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  4          7
REACTION   (26-FE-56(A,N)28-NI-59,PAR,DA)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3CPRAEP) HI-13. The pulsed tandem accelerator at
           the angles of 20-140 degr. was used.
STATUS     (CURVE,,B.V.Zhuravlev+,S,ISINN-16,237,2009) Figs 2-5
HISTORY    (20260113A) SD: SF5=PAR added to REACTION code.
           FLAG deleted (information moved to cols E-MIN/MAX).
           Data from Subents 003-008 were added.
ENDBIB               7
